### [Ziqian Xia](https://ziqian-xia.tech/)
:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="40%"}
![](pics/avatar.jpg){width=150}
:::

::: {.column width="60%"}

Ziqian Xia is a graduate student at Tongji University, China. Ziqian's research interests lie at the intersection of human behavior, technology, and environmental conservation. Ziqian's journey has been marked by a passionate pursuit of understanding the human dimension of climate change. Ziqian's  contributions to a myriad of publications, including *Nature Reviews Psychology*, *Journal of Cleaner Production*, *Environmental Research Letters*, and *Resources, Conservation and Recycling*.

Contact: [ziqian.research@gmail.com](mailto:ziqian.research@gmail.com)
:::

::::



### Jinquan Ye
:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="40%"}
![](pics/yjq.jpeg){width=150}
:::

::: {.column width="60%"}

Jinquan Ye is a master student degree in environmental policy at the Nicholas School of the Environment at Duke University, and he is looking for a future PhD position. He is currently researching the application of LLM (Large Language Model) to the field of environmental policy and meta-analysis. His interests include: Climate change mitigation: he is interested in how policy instruments can be used to reduce greenhouse gas emissions in order to slow the rate of global warming. Natural Language Processing. Meta-analysis. LLM (Large Language Model): He is exploring how LLM can be applied to the field of environmental policy to improve the efficiency of policy formulation and implementation.

Contact: [jinquan.ye@duke.edu](mailto:jinquan.ye@duke.edu)
:::

::::


### Jianxun Yang

Dr. Jianxun Yang is a distinguished postdoctoral researcher at Nanjing University, specializing in the intricate intersections of climate change adaptation, environmental psychology, climate risk assessment, and the potential of environmental big data. His research portfolio is marked by a deep commitment to understanding and addressing the multifaceted challenges of climate change and environmental degradation.

Contact: [yangjx@nju.edu.cn ](mailto:yangjx@nju.edu.cn )

